rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-2651

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-3074
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-3075
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-3076

Description:
    Previous versions of the vim package contain multiple vulnerabilities,
    the most serious of which allow user-assisted attackers to execute
    arbitrary commands via maliciously crafted file and directory names.

